==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strath
<hw>Strath</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael.
<ets>srath</ets>.]</ety> <def>A valley of considerable size, through
which a river runs; a valley bottom; -- often used in composition with
the name of the river; <as>as, <ex>Strath</ex> Spey, <ex>Strath</ex>don,
<ex>Strath</ex>more</as>.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The long green <qex>strath</qex> of Napa valley.</q> <rj><qau>R.
L. Stevenson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strathspey</ent>⟦br⟧
